body.description: Maspen USB Flash Drive Basic InformationChip: Grade A, original brand flash memory chipCapacity: 32 GQuantity: 2 packColor: Black,BlueSize: 2.13"*0.76"*0.4" (fold) Interface: USB 2.0 (Backwards compatible to USB 1.1) Durability: 50,000 times read and writeCompatibility: Desktop, Laptop, Macintosh, Tablet, Speakers, Television, Car Video (which has USB port and allows data transmission) and all with USB portOperating System: Windows 7/Vista/XP/2000/ME/NT/98, Linux and Mac OSMaspen USB Thumb Drive Features: * Safe: Every piece tested and formatted via the specific machine before delivery; * 360°Metal Swivel Cap: 360° rotation round the ABS plastic body, can protect USB connector, no need to find your cap everywhere and avoid to lose it* LED Indicator: This USB jump drives have a light that flashes when uploading / downloading files to it* Anti-skidding Surface: The flash drive has matt surface cap and ABS plastic rubber oil skin feeling finished body to avoid to leave your fingerprint on it* Keyring Design: The end of the usb memory sticks have a loop for a lanyard or key ring to keep it safe or on your keys* Unbranded USB Thumb Drive: Print your logo or memo on the zip drives as you wish to your customers or employeesPackage: 2 Pack of 32GB USB Flash Drives Please Note:Some of the listed capacity on the USB flash drives is used for formatting and other functions, thus is not available for data storage. As such, the actual available capacity for data storage is less than what is listed on the products.Tips: * FAT32 is factory default drive format, which is read/write compatible with Windows and Mac OS; while NTFS is compatible with Windows but semi-compatible with Mac OS. Please format it properly if need* FAT32 cannot support a single file up to 4GB, please reformat to NTFS or exFAT if need

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Work okay for small temporary storage
reviews.reviewText: If you need relatively small amounts of storage for moving items from one computer to another (for example) or something similar, these work fine, but they don't hold much and, in my experience, they don't last long, maybe a half dozens uses, before going bad. So, they're a quick, cheap, easy solution to some things, but I wouldn't suggest them for long term storage.
